<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1124">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/32.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith a
                            copy of a telegram dated May 1, from the special representative of the
                            Department of State at El Paso, Texas, quoting a telegram received by
                            him, under date of the 30th ultimo, from General Carranza, in relation
                            to the resumption of work in the Tampico oil district.</p>
                        <p>I beg to request that the text of this telegram from General Carranza be
                            immediately telegraphed to Admiral Fletcher, for his information.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>